what is the difference between Props and State? explore ?
-->props are used to pass data from oe component to another.thestate is local data storage that is local to the component only and cannot be passed to other component.
this setState property is used to update the state value in the component.
Explain the useState API?explore?
-->The useState() is a Hook that allows you to have state variables in functional components . so basically useState is the ability to encapsulate local state in a functional component.
